HEADWORD: Keno
<hw>Ke"no</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>quine</ets>
five winning numbers, fr. L. <ets>quini</ets> five each,
<ets>quinque</ets> five. See <er>Five</er>.]</ety> <def>A gambling game,
a variety of the game of lotto, played with balls or knobs, numbered,
and cards also numbered.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

